WEBVTT

00:00.239 --> 00:01.839
Previously on The Fosters...

00:01.940 --> 00:05.310
- What's up, good lookin'?
- Idiot.

00:06.776 --> 00:09.010
You wanna kill somebody?
It ain't gonna be us.

00:09.045 --> 00:11.045
- Hey, Callie.
- Hey.

00:11.080 --> 00:12.647
Do you forgive me?

00:12.682 --> 00:15.016
You were hands down the best Juliet.

00:15.051 --> 00:16.067
Would you be in my musical?

00:16.119 --> 00:17.618
You canceled the check?

00:17.654 --> 00:18.970
The one you stole
from me? You bet I did.

00:19.005 --> 00:20.888
I hate you, and Daddy hated you too,

00:20.890 --> 00:23.007
and that's why he killed himself.

00:23.042 --> 00:25.793
We got all the plants
and materials donated

00:25.828 --> 00:26.827
thanks to Monte!

00:26.879 --> 00:28.729
- So have you read it, the bill?
- No.

00:28.765 --> 00:31.666
I just don't like seeing kids
being sold to the higher bidders.

00:31.701 --> 00:33.701
And let's be honest, Rita,
you have your own agenda.

00:33.736 --> 00:34.769
That's what you think of me?

00:34.804 --> 00:36.621
I'm kind of worried about Jesus.

00:36.673 --> 00:37.738
He found our birth dad.

00:37.774 --> 00:39.056
The guy's a sex offender.

00:39.092 --> 00:40.658
He's on that list because of me.

00:40.693 --> 00:42.710
I was 15, he was 18.

00:42.712 --> 00:44.095
I don't know what you're looking for.

00:44.130 --> 00:46.948
I'm not your father and I never will be.

00:52.121 --> 00:53.921
Mariana, watch it please!

00:53.957 --> 00:54.889
Sorry, Mom.

00:56.659 --> 00:59.794
Emotional Intelligence. What's that?

00:59.846 --> 01:02.863
It's the ability to express
your emotions in a positive way.

01:02.899 --> 01:04.799
Your EQ instead of your IQ.

01:04.834 --> 01:07.735
So you're, like, taking a class?

01:07.787 --> 01:09.837
No, I'm teaching a class as part of
the department's Youth Outreach Program.

01:09.839 --> 01:12.740
No offense, but who would
want to take a class like this?

01:12.775 --> 01:15.042
Kids who have a choice between
it and juvie, that's who.

01:15.044 --> 01:17.645
"What is an appropriate
response to anger?

01:17.680 --> 01:20.715
"'A', beat someone
up, 'B', start a fire,

01:20.750 --> 01:22.650
'C', get drunk,

01:22.702 --> 01:24.952
'D', express your feelings
with words?" Seriously?

01:25.004 --> 01:26.053
For this kids that I am teaching

01:26.089 --> 01:29.040
who don't have good
parenting or a stable home,

01:29.092 --> 01:31.859
'D' is not necessarily the
obvious choice, Mariana.

01:31.894 --> 01:34.912
Hey, check it out.

01:34.964 --> 01:37.798
- Oh, my gosh.
- Wow! I love it!

01:37.834 --> 01:39.867
- Wow, Brandon.
- That is amazing.

01:39.902 --> 01:40.868
Yeah, Mat designed it.

01:40.870 --> 01:43.721
Hm. Well, it must have been hard

01:43.773 --> 01:44.772
with Zoey's tongue down his throat.

01:44.824 --> 01:46.791
- Hey!
- Mat's dating Zoey?

01:46.843 --> 01:49.677
Yeah, and I find it very
unprofessional if you ask me,

01:49.712 --> 01:51.746
but the director totally rejected

01:51.781 --> 01:53.731
the idea of a no dating policy, so...

01:53.766 --> 01:55.983
Oh, please. You just don't
want to see Mat with anyone else

01:56.035 --> 01:57.918
even though you're dating
that Nick guy or whatever.

01:57.920 --> 01:59.086
I am not.

01:59.138 --> 02:01.022
I went on one date with him
and it was a total disaster.

02:01.024 --> 02:01.989
Why? What happened?

02:03.926 --> 02:04.892
Nothing. It was just boring.

02:06.017 --> 02:07.016
Uh, well, Brandon,

02:07.018 --> 02:09.818
I think that poster is
absolutely beautiful.

02:09.854 --> 02:10.886
I'm very proud of you,

02:10.922 --> 02:12.822
how hard you've been working
on your senior project.

02:12.857 --> 02:15.758
Yeah, I guess I didn't realize how
much time it would take exactly.

02:15.810 --> 02:17.760
Well, what about your
Juilliard audition?

02:17.795 --> 02:19.628
You know, don't drop
the ball on that please.

02:19.664 --> 02:21.647
Oh, no. I... I won't.
Um, I... I've got time.

02:21.699 --> 02:23.666
Mom, I actually... I
wanted to ask you, um,

02:23.701 --> 02:25.017
do you think we could
rehearse on the gym stage?

02:25.053 --> 02:26.702
It's just that the art room
is getting a little small

02:26.738 --> 02:28.671
- now that we're casting the other parts.
- I'll talk to Monte,

02:28.706 --> 02:29.972
- but I don't see why not.
- All right.

02:30.008 --> 02:31.640
Okay, everybody. Come
on. Let's get a move on.

02:31.693 --> 02:33.609
Jesus, you gonna put some
clothes on sometime today?

02:33.661 --> 02:34.927
I don't have a first period today.

02:34.962 --> 02:36.045
My teacher's at a conference.

02:36.047 --> 02:37.897
What kind of school
you runnin' over there?

02:37.949 --> 02:40.016
Oh, and hey, and listen, Mike
is out of town for a little bit,

02:40.051 --> 02:41.967
so AJ's gonna stay with us.

02:42.020 --> 02:44.787
- For how long?
- Just a couple of days.

02:44.822 --> 02:46.005
Jude doesn't get back from
his school trip until Friday,

02:46.057 --> 02:47.757
so he can sleep in his bed.

02:47.792 --> 02:48.908
Great, I finally get the room to myself,

02:48.943 --> 02:50.793
and now I gotta share it again?

02:50.828 --> 02:51.827
You know what?

02:51.863 --> 02:53.896
May I have your b... b...

02:53.931 --> 02:55.781
Thank you, Callie.

02:55.833 --> 02:59.602
So, uh, there's something
I need to tell you.

02:59.637 --> 03:00.653
Something you should know.

03:00.705 --> 03:02.655
Um, AJ and I are kind of dating.

03:03.725 --> 03:06.609
Oh. Sorry. I... I forgot my poster.

03:09.047 --> 03:10.930
Uh... okay.

03:10.982 --> 03:13.866
Well, we're not fostering
him, so I guess there's not

03:13.918 --> 03:15.551
an illegal issue if he stays here.

03:15.603 --> 03:17.553
But as with any boyfriend in the house,

03:17.588 --> 03:18.838
we expect you to follow the rules.

03:18.873 --> 03:20.005
You know, no hanging
out behind closed doors.

03:20.058 --> 03:21.023
Oh, of course not.

03:21.059 --> 03:22.858
Thank you for telling us.

03:24.829 --> 03:25.961
Is anyone home?

